{
  "stem": "1062.3",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was-- I was in Buna till January 18, 1945.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And see what happened already, the Russian armies they started to approach Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had an order to evacuate us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that morning, we didn't go out to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that point?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I thought that they are someplace alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I'll tell you a story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was always thinking to myself when I was there, you know, and seen what I'd seen, and things like this, and I was a young boy-- I was 16 years old.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I always said to myself, this is going to be over.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm going to see my mother, and I'm going to see my everybody from my old village.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I'm going to tell them stories about what happened to me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They wouldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I always thought to myself that I'm going to meet them and I'm going to tell them a story of what happened to me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know it's an unbelievable story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I, as far as I'm concerned, and I could tell you that I remember.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I have a good memory.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't believe that people knew, even when you were in Auschwitz-- except those that worked in-- there was a kommando, which sonderkommando, Kanada kommando, and they were in charge with taking of the people off the train.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We asked them, and stuff-- they knew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But even if they would tell it to somebody-- first of all nobody, you know, they wouldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I am telling you, I always hoped-- and I could show you downstairs, I have-- where I searched for my family after the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I still thought they are alive.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
